  "abstract": "Chickpea (Cicer arietinum L.) is one of the most\r\nimportant grain legumes in Nepal. It is a major\r\nsource of protein and forms an integral part of\r\nthe Nepalese diet. Constraints to chickpea,\r\nhowever, include the disease botrytis grey mold\r\n(BGM) and the pod borer insect (Helicoverpa\r\narmigera). The result was a sharp decline in\r\nchickpea production due to increasing losses,\r\neven up to 100%.",
